</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF94FFF6FF2F001537ABFD63" blockId="3.[227,1233,613,640]" box="[227,1233,613,640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">Labral frontal edge with a shallow emargination medially. Anterior margin of</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1958E8FF94FFF6FF6104EB3009F92F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453267" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453267/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="348" startId="3.[173,206,1691,1713]" targetBox="[214,1184,687,1656]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF94FFF6FF6104EB3009F92F" blockId="3.[173,1232,1691,1740]" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">
Fig. 3. Epipharynx of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF94FFF6FEB504EC3171F952" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[377,523,1691,1713]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rumicis">
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FEB504EC3171F952" box="[377,523,1691,1713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">Hypera rumicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FDD904EC315BF952" box="[533,545,1692,1713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">a</emphasis>
— II instar larva, general view; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FC8104EB3023F952" box="[845,857,1691,1713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">b</emphasis>
— median impression; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FBF704EC373EF952" box="[1083,1092,1692,1713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">c</emphasis>
— apical excision; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FF2D04C63397F92F" box="[225,237,1718,1740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">d</emphasis>
— the same of mature larva. Scale bars: 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FDA304C73101F92F" box="[623,635,1719,1740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FD4A04C631D3F92F" box="[646,681,1718,1740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">b, d</emphasis>
— 10 μm, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FCDD04C73060F92F" box="[785,794,1719,1740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">c</emphasis>
— 1 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF94FFF6FF61049B3260F8D5" blockId="3.[173,1232,1771,1846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">
Рис. 3. Эпифаринкс 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF94FFF6FE4D049C316FF8E2" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[385,533,1771,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rumicis">
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FE4D049C316FF8E2" box="[385,533,1771,1793]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">Hypera rumicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FDEE049C3154F8E2" box="[546,558,1772,1793]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">a</emphasis>
— личинка второго возраста, общий вид; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FC20049B3082F8E2" box="[1004,1016,1771,1793]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">b</emphasis>
— серединное вдавление; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FF3805773387F8FF" box="[244,253,1799,1820]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">c</emphasis>
— вершинная вырезка; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FE360576317CF8FF" box="[506,518,1798,1820]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">d</emphasis>
— то же взрослой личинки. Масштабные линейки: 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FBEE05773754F8FF" box="[1058,1070,1799,1820]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FBF605763724F8FF" box="[1082,1118,1798,1820]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">b, d</emphasis>
— 10 мкм, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF94FFF6FF61055133CCF8D5" box="[173,182,1825,1846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="348">c</emphasis>
— 1 мкм.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF93FFF1FF6A02DF370BFE69" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
epipharynx with the central flattened subtrapezoidal excision. Labral rods convergent and prominent, epipharyngeal surface with three depressions. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FCF202BF3000FF13" box="[830,890,207,240]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
Als 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FCAE02923000FF13" attach="left" box="[866,890,226,240]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">1–3</subScript>
</emphasis>
short, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FC0502A03082FF0A" box="[969,1016,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">ams</emphasis>
very short, placed near frontal edge of epipharynx, behind them located 2 sensillae (reduced or broken 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FBBB028037D7FEF3" box="[1143,1197,240,272]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
ams 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FB69037237D7FEF3" attach="left" box="[1189,1197,258,272]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
?), 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FF6A036033A0FED3" box="[166,218,272,304]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FF1E035233A0FED3" attach="left" box="[210,218,290,304]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
short, placed near the base of central emargination. Consisted of 2 sensillae 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FB8403603715FECA" box="[1096,1135,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">snp</emphasis>
located posterolaterally of 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FEB5034032D7FEB3" box="[377,429,304,336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FE69033232D7FEB3" attach="left" box="[421,429,322,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
approximately in the middle of epipharynx. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FC68034030A1FEB3" box="[932,987,304,336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
Mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FC1F033230A1FEB3" attach="left" box="[979,987,322,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
placed posteriorly of 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FF6A032033B7FE8A" box="[166,205,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">snp</emphasis>
. 2 sensillae located laterally of 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FDE803203122FE93" box="[548,600,336,368]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FD9C03123122FE93" attach="left" box="[592,600,354,368]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 2 pairs of sensillae posteriolaterad on basal parts of labral rods. Distal part of epipharyngeal surface with series of dentiform appendages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
